HEADWORD: Footlight
<hw>Foot"light`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>One of a row of
lights in the front of the stage in a theater, etc., and on a level
therewith.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Before the footlights</b></col>, <cd>upon the stage; --
hence, in the capacity of an actor.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>footling</ent>⟦br⟧
